{"article_id":"slvVWPIxueBmGqIc","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Justin Trudeau 's Liberal Party has retained power in a narrow Canadian election win","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"but he will now be prime minister of a minority government .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"The Liberals are projected to win 157 seats , 13 short of a majority ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"and will find it harder to pass legislation in Mr Trudeau 's second term .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"The opposition Conservatives are expected to win the popular vote","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"but have not translated that into seats .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"They are projected to take 121 , up from the 95","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"they held before .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Although Monday night 's results saw a sharp decline in seats for the country 's left-leaning New Democratic Party","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"( NDP ) ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"its leader , Jagmeet Singh , could become the kingmaker .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"The NDP is projected to take 24 seats in the 338-seat parliament .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"Quebec 's separatist party , the Bloc Québécois ,","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"which competes only in that province ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"fared much better .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"It is expected to take 32 seats ,","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"compared to the 10","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"it won in 2015 .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"The federal election was seen as a referendum on Mr Trudeau ,","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"who had a bumpy first term ,","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"tainted by scandal .","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"Mr Trudeau told cheering supporters in Montreal","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"that voters had `` rejected division and negativity ...","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"and they rejected cuts and austerity","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"and voted in favour of a progressive agenda and strong action on climate change '' .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"He said :","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"`` Thank you for having faith in us","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"to move our country in the right direction . ''","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"And to those","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"who did not back him ,","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"he promised","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"his party would govern for everyone .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"His weakened grip on power is being seen as a rebuke of his record","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"but the result is bitterly disappointing for Conservative leader Andrew Scheer .","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"Mr Trudeau swept into power in 2015","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"promising `` real change '' and a slew of progressive pledges .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"But after four years in power , Mr Trudeau faced criticism for his ability","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"to follow through .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"His environmental record , for example , has been undercut by his support for the Trans Mountain oil pipeline expansion project .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"And Mr Trudeau 's vow","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"to institute federal electoral reform","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"was quickly abandoned ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"angering some left-leaning voters excited by the prospect","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"of seeing an alternative voting system","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Still ,","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"according to an independent assessment by two dozen Canadian academics ,","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"Mr Trudeau has kept - fully or partially -","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"92 % of these promises , the most by any Canadian government in 35 years .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"An ethics scandal early this year ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"known as the SNC-Lavalin affair ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"took a major toll on his support .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"Last month an ethics watchdog found","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"the prime minister had violated federal conflict of interest rules","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"by improperly trying to influence a former minister in relation to a criminal trial","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"facing major Canadian engineering firm SNC-Lavalin .","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"Mr Trudeau 's election odds then seemed at risk","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"when images of the prime minister","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"wearing blackface make-up in three separate instances","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"were widely circulated .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"The images were seen as a major hit to Mr Trudeau 's cultivated political image ,","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"characterised by compassion and inclusion .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"In his speech , Mr Trudeau also addressed Quebec and the provinces in western Canada ,","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"where his party had not fared well ,","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"saying :","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"`` I 've heard your frustration . ''","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Skip","depth":4},{"id":66,"text":"Twitter post by @ JustinTrudeau","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"Thank you , Canada ,","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"for putting your trust in our team","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"and for having faith in us","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"to move this country in the right direction .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Regardless of how you cast your vote ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"our team will work hard for all Canadians .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"- Justin Trudeau","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"( @ JustinTrudeau )","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"October 22 , 2019","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"Report","depth":4},{"id":77,"text":"Mr Scheer said","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"he was `` incredibly proud '' of the larger Conservative team","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"going to Ottawa .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"the country was `` further divided ''","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"and that his party had put Mr Trudeau `` on notice ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"his leadership is damaged","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"and his government will end soon '' .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"The Conservatives are projected to take 34.4 % of the popular vote ,","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"compared to the Liberals ' 33 % .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"However , the first-past-the-post system","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"- awarding victory to the candidate with most votes in any given constituency -","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"means that has not translated to seats","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"won .","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Speaking from his home district in Burnaby , British Columbia ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"Mr Singh acknowledged some disappointing results","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"but focused on the future ,","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"promising to make `` Canadians ' life ... better '' .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Green Party leader Elizabeth May said","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"the election had been a success .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"It is expected to take three seats ,","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"compared to one in 2015 .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"US President Donald Trump and UK PM Boris Johnson tweeted congratulations to Mr Trudeau .","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"Skip Twitter post by @ realDonaldTrump","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"Congratulations to @ JustinTrudeau on a wonderful and hard fought victory .","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"Canada is well served .","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"I look forward to working with you toward the betterment of both of our countries !","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"October 22 , 2019 Report","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"Skip Twitter post by @ 10DowningStreet","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"\" Congratulations @ JustinTrudeau on your re-election .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"As Commonwealth , NATO , and Five Eyes partners the UK and Canada share history and values","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"and I look forward to continuing to work with you on priorities such as girls ' education and climate change. \"","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"- PM @ BorisJohnson 🇬🇧🇨🇦","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"- UK Prime Minister","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"( @ 10DowningStreet )","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"October 22 , 2019 Report","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"Minority governments are not uncommon -","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"there have been three in the past 15 years .","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"A coalition government , however , is rare .","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"It was last attempted in 2008 by the Liberals and NDP ,","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"but was disbanded","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"when then-Prime Minister Stephen Harper , a Conservative , prorogued parliament .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"Analysts believe","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"the obvious link would again be between the Liberals and the NDP .","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"They also believe","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"the Bloc Québécois","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"-","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"which has softened its stance on demands for independence -","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"will neither enter a coalition","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"nor force another election .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"Indeed , in his post-results speech , Bloc leader Yves-François Blanchet said :","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"`` We have to find a way","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"to make this parliament work . ''","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"Without any agreed coalition , Mr Trudeau would clearly need to compromise","depth":6},{"id":133,"text":"to get policies through .","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"Mr Scheer will have to assess his position .","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"He pitched himself to Canadians as the candidate","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"speaking up for issues","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"which directly affect voters ' lives and wallets .","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"But instead he faced scrutiny over where the Conservative Party stood on gay marriage and abortion .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":277,"left":172,"right":276,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":156,"right":171,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":146,"right":155,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":146,"left":142,"right":145,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":142,"left":140,"right":141,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":141,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":4,"right":144,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":144,"left":5,"right":143,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":149,"right":154,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":148,"right":11,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":147,"right":10,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":147,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":151,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":150,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":150,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":15,"right":152,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":169,"right":170,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":158,"right":168,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":18,"right":157,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity